to\": 98}, {\"ngram\": \"Paid press releases\", \"from\": 113, \"to\": 132}, {\"ngram\": \"Advertise\", \"from\": 133, \"to\": 142}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 164, \"to\": 166}, {\"ngram\": \"the biggest sports news\", \"from\": 183, \"to\": 206}, {\"ngram\": \"your inbox\", \"from\": 210, \"to\": 220}, {\"ngram\": \"French gendarmes\", \"from\": 221, \"to\": 237}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 262, \"to\": 266}, {\"ngram\": \"a rehearsal\", \"from\": 270, \"to\": 281}, {\"ngram\": \"the Seine river\", \"from\": 285, \"to\": 300}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris 2024 Olympic Games\", \"from\": 329, \"to\": 357}, {\"ngram\": \"June\", \"from\": 361, \"to\": 365}]}, {\"sentence\": \"PHOTO: AFP PublishedJun 24, 2024, 08:49 PM UpdatedJun 25, 2024, 12:43 AM PARIS-The river Seine is set to be a star feature of the Paris Olympics, but heavy rain, pollution and security fears mean there is still suspense around its role just one month out from the start.\", \"from\": 389, \"to\": 662, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"PHOTO\", \"from\": 389, \"to\": 394}, {\"ngram\": \"AFP PublishedJun\", \"from\": 396, \"to\": 412}, {\"ngram\": \"08:49 PM\", \"from\": 423, \"to\": 431}, {\"ngram\": \"UpdatedJun\", \"from\": 432, \"to\": 442}, {\"ngram\": \"12:43 AM PARIS-The river Seine\", \"from\": 453, \"to\": 483}, {\"ngram\": \"a star feature\", \"from\": 497, \"to\": 511}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 515, \"to\": 533}, {\"ngram\": \"heavy rain, pollution and security fears\", \"from\": 539, \"to\": 579}, {\"ngram\": \"suspense\", \"from\": 600, \"to\": 608}, {\"ngram\": \"its role\", \"from\": 616, \"to\": 624}, {\"ngram\": \"the start\", \"from\": 649, \"to\": 658}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A spectacular July 26 opening ceremony has beenplanned along the famed waterway- the first time the Olympics have begun outside the main stadium - and it will also host open-water swimming and a leg of the triathlon.\", \"from\": 664, \"to\": 880, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A spectacular July 26 opening ceremony\", \"from\": 664, \"to\": 702}, {\"ngram\": \"the famed waterway-\", \"from\": 725, \"to\": 744}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 760, \"to\": 772}, {\"ngram\": \"the main stadium\", \"from\": 792, \"to\": 808}, {\"ngram\": \"open-water swimming\", \"from\": 833, \"to\": 852}, {\"ngram\": \"a leg\", \"from\": 857, \"to\": 862}, {\"ngram\": \"the triathlon\", \"from\": 866, \"to\": 879}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But, with the clock ticking down, the river is flowing too fast for rehearsals and istoo dirty for sport.\", \"from\": 881, \"to\": 986, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the clock\", \"from\": 891, \"to\": 900}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 915, \"to\": 924}, {\"ngram\": \"rehearsals\", \"from\": 949, \"to\": 959}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 980, \"to\": 985}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With currents unusually strong, organisers cancelled the first full practice session for the opening ceremony scheduled for June 24 involving all 85 river boats which will carry athletes along a 6km route.\", \"from\": 988, \"to\": 1193, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"currents\", \"from\": 993, \"to\": 1001}, {\"ngram\": \"organisers\", \"from\": 1020, \"to\": 1030}, {\"ngram\": \"the first full practice session\", \"from\": 1041, \"to\": 1072}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 1077, \"to\": 1097}, {\"ngram\": \"June\", \"from\": 1112, \"to\": 1116}, {\"ngram\": \"all 85 river boats\", \"from\": 1130, \"to\": 1148}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1166, \"to\": 1174}, {\"ngram\": \"a 6km route\", \"from\": 1181, \"to\": 1192}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If the flow is too fast, it will pose a serious problem for the opening ceremony,\\\" hydrologist Jean-Marie Mouchel told AFP.\", \"from\": 1195, \"to\": 1319, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1302, \"end\": 1309, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mouchel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1879116617357387e-15, \"text\": \"Mouchel\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mouchel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mouchel\"}, {\"begin\": 1315, \"end\": 1318, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"score\": 0.9999999997216946, \"rank\": 2.5272105611963453e-10, \"text\": \"AFP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the flow\", \"from\": 1199, \"to\": 1207}, {\"ngram\": \"a serious problem\", \"from\": 1234, \"to\": 1251}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 1256, \"to\": 1276}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After weeks of unusually wet weather, the Seine is high up its banks, with its flow measured at 500 cubic metres per second on June 21 - around four to five times higher than its usual level in the summer months.\", \"from\": 1321, \"to\": 1533, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1363, \"end\": 1368, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2932664395904922e-13, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"weeks\", \"from\": 1327, \"to\": 1332}, {\"ngram\": \"unusually wet weather\", \"from\": 1336, \"to\": 1357}, {\"ngram\": \"its banks\", \"from\": 1380, \"to\": 1389}, {\"ngram\": \"its flow\", \"from\": 1396, \"to\": 1404}, {\"ngram\": \"500 cubic metres\", \"from\": 1417, \"to\": 1433}, {\"ngram\": \"second\", \"from\": 1438, \"to\": 1444}, {\"ngram\": \"June\", \"from\": 1448, \"to\": 1452}, {\"ngram\": \"its usual level\", \"from\": 1496, \"to\": 1511}, {\"ngram\": \"the summer months\", \"from\": 1515, \"to\": 1532}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The heavy rain in May and June has also caused major pollution problems.\", \"from\": 1535, \"to\": 1607, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The heavy rain\", \"from\": 1535, \"to\": 1549}, {\"ngram\": \"May\", \"from\": 1553, \"to\": 1556}, {\"ngram\": \"June\", \"from\": 1561, \"to\": 1565}, {\"ngram\": \"major pollution problems\", \"from\": 1582, \"to\": 1606}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French authorities have spent \\u20ac1.4 billion (S$2 billion) in the last decade trying to clean up the river by improving the Paris sewerage system, as well as building new water treatment and storage facilities.\", \"from\": 1608, \"to\": 1820, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1612, \"end\": 1618, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.7420559583497812, \"rank\": 0.2684536616656853, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1734, \"end\": 1739, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0436845493038187e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"S$2\", \"from\": 1656, \"to\": 1659}, {\"ngram\": \"the last decade\", \"from\": 1672, \"to\": 1687}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 1707, \"to\": 1716}, {\"ngram\": \"new water treatment and storage facilities\", \"from\": 1777, \"to\": 1819}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But major storms still overwhelm the wastewater network, some of which dates back to the 19th century, leading to discharges of untreated sewage directly into the river.\", \"from\": 1822, \"to\": 1991, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"major storms\", \"from\": 1826, \"to\": 1838}, {\"ngram\": \"the wastewater network\", \"from\": 1855, \"to\": 1877}, {\"ngram\": \"the 19th century\", \"from\": 1907, \"to\": 1923}, {\"ngram\": \"discharges\", \"from\": 1936, \"to\": 1946}, {\"ngram\": \"untreated sewage\", \"from\": 1950, \"to\": 1966}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 1981, \"to\": 1990}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Test results published on June 21 showed levels of E. Coli bacteria - a key indicator of faecal matter - were often twice as high as the maximum permitted limit for Olympic swimming during June 10 to 16.\", \"from\": 1993, \"to\": 2196, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Test results\", \"from\": 1993, \"to\": 2005}, {\"ngram\": \"June\", \"from\": 2019, \"to\": 2023}, {\"ngram\": \"levels\", \"from\": 2034, \"to\": 2040}, {\"ngram\": \"E. Coli bacteria\", \"from\": 2044, \"to\": 2060}, {\"ngram\": \"a key indicator\", \"from\": 2063, \"to\": 2078}, {\"ngram\": \"faecal matter\", \"from\": 2082, \"to\": 2095}, {\"ngram\": \"the maximum permitted limit\", \"from\": 2126, \"to\": 2153}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic swimming\", \"from\": 2158, \"to\": 2174}, {\"ngram\": \"June\", \"from\": 2182, \"to\": 2186}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is no doubt that the water quality is not there yet,\\\" said the top government official for the Paris region, Marc Guillaume, while remaining optimistic that dry summer weather would resolve the problem.\", \"from\": 2198, \"to\": 2407, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2300, \"end\": 2305, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0436845493038187e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no doubt\", \"from\": 2208, \"to\": 2216}, {\"ngram\": \"the water quality\", \"from\": 2222, \"to\": 2239}, {\"ngram\": \"the top government official\", \"from\": 2264, \"to\": 2291}, {\"ngram\": \"Marc Guillaume\", \"from\": 2314, \"to\": 2328}, {\"ngram\": \"dry summer weather\", \"from\": 2362, \"to\": 2380}, {\"ngram\": \"the problem\", \"from\": 2395, \"to\": 2406}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The latest readings \\\"are not in line with the standards we will have in the summer\\\", he added.\", \"from\": 2409, \"to\": 2503, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The latest readings\", \"from\": 2409, \"to\": 2428}, {\"ngram\": \"line\", \"from\": 2441, \"to\": 2445}, {\"ngram\": \"the standards\", \"from\": 2451, \"to\": 2464}, {\"ngram\": \"the summer\", \"from\": 2481, \"to\": 2491}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris Mayor Anne Hidalgo, who wants to create public swimming spots in the river in 2025, had to postpone a much-publicised dip to demonstrate its cleanliness on June 23.\", \"from\": 2505, \"to\": 2675, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2505, \"end\": 2516, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Mayor\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2517, \"end\": 2529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anne Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"public swimming spots\", \"from\": 2551, \"to\": 2572}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 2576, \"to\": 2585}, {\"ngram\": \"a much-publicised dip\", \"from\": 2611, \"to\": 2632}, {\"ngram\": \"its cleanliness\", \"from\": 2648, \"to\": 2663}, {\"ngram\": \"June\", \"from\": 2667, \"to\": 2671}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She has promised to take to the water during the week of July 14.\", \"from\": 2676, \"to\": 2741, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the water\", \"from\": 2704, \"to\": 2713}, {\"ngram\": \"the week\", \"from\": 2721, \"to\": 2729}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 2733, \"to\": 2737}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The opening ceremony is also still giving members ofFrance's security forces sleepless nights, given the number of people involved and the difficulty in securing such a large area.\", \"from\": 2743, \"to\": 2923, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The opening ceremony\", \"from\": 2743, \"to\": 2763}, {\"ngram\": \"members\", \"from\": 2785, \"to\": 2792}, {\"ngram\": \"ofFrance's security forces\", \"from\": 2793, \"to\": 2819}, {\"ngram\": \"the number\", \"from\": 2844, \"to\": 2854}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 2858, \"to\": 2864}, {\"ngram\": \"the difficulty\", \"from\": 2878, \"to\": 2892}, {\"ngram\": \"such a large area\", \"from\": 2905, \"to\": 2922}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A total of 326,000 people will have tickets to watch the river parade, with hundreds of thousands of others set to observe from balconies and open windows.\", \"from\": 2925, \"to\": 3080, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A total\", \"from\": 2925, \"to\": 2932}, {\"ngram\": \"326,000 people\", \"from\": 2936, \"to\": 2950}, {\"ngram\": \"tickets\", \"from\": 2961, \"to\": 2968}, {\"ngram\": \"the river parade\", \"from\": 2978, \"to\": 2994}, {\"ngram\": \"hundreds of thousands\", \"from\": 3001, \"to\": 3022}, {\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 3026, \"to\": 3032}, {\"ngram\": \"balconies\", \"from\": 3053, \"to\": 3062}, {\"ngram\": \"open windows\", \"from\": 3067, \"to\": 3079}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The number of buildings overlooking the river complicates the security operation at a time of heightened fears about terrorism, leading to opposition in the past from senior policing figures.\", \"from\": 3082, \"to\": 3273, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The number\", \"from\": 3082, \"to\": 3092}, {\"ngram\": \"buildings\", \"from\": 3096, \"to\": 3105}, {\"ngram\": \"the security operation\", \"from\": 3140, \"to\": 3162}, {\"ngram\": \"a time\", \"from\": 3166, \"to\": 3172}, {\"ngram\": \"heightened fears\", \"from\": 3176, \"to\": 3192}, {\"ngram\": \"terrorism\", \"from\": 3199, \"to\": 3208}, {\"ngram\": \"opposition\", \"from\": 3221, \"to\": 3231}, {\"ngram\": \"the past\", \"from\": 3235, \"to\": 3243}, {\"ngram\": \"senior policing figures\", \"from\": 3249, \"to\": 3272}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Snipers will be positioned on the top of every building in the immediate vicinity, with a total of 45,000 security force personnel set to be deployed.\", \"from\": 3275, \"to\": 3425, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Snipers\", \"from\": 3275, \"to\": 3282}, {\"ngram\": \"the top\", \"from\": 3305, \"to\": 3312}, {\"ngram\": \"every building\", \"from\": 3316, \"to\": 3330}, {\"ngram\": \"the immediate vicinity\", \"from\": 3334, \"to\": 3356}, {\"ngram\": \"a total\", \"from\": 3363, \"to\": 3370}, {\"ngram\": \"45,000 security force personnel\", \"from\": 3374, \"to\": 3405}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The opening ceremony is what's worrying us the most,\\\" one senior police figure told AFP recently on condition of anonymity.\", \"from\": 3427, \"to\": 3551, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3512, \"end\": 3515, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"score\": 0.9999999997216946, \"rank\": 2.5272105611963453e-10, \"text\": \"AFP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The opening ceremony\", \"from\": 3428, \"to\": 3448}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 3468, \"to\": 3470}, {\"ngram\": \"one senior police figure\", \"from\": 3482, \"to\": 3506}, {\"ngram\": \"condition\", \"from\": 3528, \"to\": 3537}, {\"ngram\": \"anonymity\", \"from\": 3541, \"to\": 3550}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Constantly asked about contingency plans in the event of credible threats to the ceremony, Paris 2024 organisers publicly insist there is no alternative to holding it on the river.\", \"from\": 3553, \"to\": 3733, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3644, \"end\": 3654, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.403086883235363e-23, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"contingency plans\", \"from\": 3576, \"to\": 3593}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 3597, \"to\": 3606}, {\"ngram\": \"credible threats\", \"from\": 3610, \"to\": 3626}, {\"ngram\": \"the ceremony\", \"from\": 3630, \"to\": 3642}, {\"ngram\": \"organisers\", \"from\": 3655, \"to\": 3665}, {\"ngram\": \"no alternative\", \"from\": 3691, \"to\": 3705}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 3723, \"to\": 3732}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Behind the scenes, sources have told AFP that one option is a much-shortened parade, which would take place over a bridge in front of the Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 3735, \"to\": 3886, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3772, \"end\": 3775, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"score\": 0.9999999997216946, \"rank\": 2.5272105611963453e-10, \"text\": \"AFP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the scenes\", \"from\": 3742, \"to\": 3752}, {\"ngram\": \"sources\", \"from\": 3754, \"to\": 3761}, {\"ngram\": \"one option\", \"from\": 3781, \"to\": 3791}, {\"ngram\": \"a much-shortened parade\", \"from\": 3795, \"to\": 3818}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 3837, \"to\": 3842}, {\"ngram\": \"a bridge\", \"from\": 3848, \"to\": 3856}, {\"ngram\": \"front\", \"from\": 3860, \"to\": 3865}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 3869, \"to\": 3885}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For the open water swimming, organisers have flexibility in the schedule, enabling them to move the event if there is a downpour.\", \"from\": 3887, \"to\": 4016, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the open water swimming\", \"from\": 3891, \"to\": 3914}, {\"ngram\": \"organisers\", \"from\": 3916, \"to\": 3926}, {\"ngram\": \"flexibility\", \"from\": 3932, \"to\": 3943}, {\"ngram\": \"the schedule\", \"from\": 3947, \"to\": 3959}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 3983, \"to\": 3992}, {\"ngram\": \"a downpour\", \"from\": 4005, \"to\": 4015}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the worst-case scenario, it would be cancelled and the triathlon would become a duathlon - just running and cycling - without the swimming.\", \"from\": 4018, \"to\": 4160, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the worst-case scenario\", \"from\": 4021, \"to\": 4044}, {\"ngram\": \"the triathlon\", \"from\": 4072, \"to\": 4085}, {\"ngram\": \"a duathlon\", \"from\": 4099, \"to\": 4109}, {\"ngram\": \"the swimming\", \"from\": 4147, \"to\": 4159}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletes are busy training and trying to ignore the noise.\", \"from\": 4162, \"to\": 4220, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Athletes\", \"from\": 4162, \"to\": 4170}, {\"ngram\": \"busy training\", \"from\": 4175, \"to\": 4188}, {\"ngram\": \"the noise\", \"from\": 4210, \"to\": 4219}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Every time there is been problems,\\\" French open water swimming coach Stephane Lecat said last week, referring to last-minute suspense around Guanabara Bay for the 2016 Rio de Janeiro Olympics and concerns about the water quality in Tokyo in 2021.\", \"from\": 4222, \"to\": 4469, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4455, \"end\": 4460, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999999571628, \"rank\": 4.263887839854494e-10, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"problems\", \"from\": 4248, \"t